question: Which Indian personality has been elected as the vice-president of the Asia Squash Federation (ASF)?
explanation: Debendranath Sarangi, who is the President of the Squash Rackets Federation of India,  has recently elected as the vice-president of the Asia Squash Federation (ASF) with two-third majority at the 37th ASF Annual General Meeting. With this, he became the 2nd Indian to become the vice-president of the ASF after N Ramachandran. Sarangi replaced Syed Razi Nawab of Pakistan.
